@Node introduction "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}
@wordwrap

  Destructive Poker is Poker-Cardgame for one player. Your aim is to play as good as possible to increase your money count. If you run out of money game will end.

  Destructive Poker has @{"chances, jokers" link changebet } and @{"doubling" link double }. Some @{"options" link tooltypes } are customable by user.

	@{"Requirements" link requirements }
	@{"Overall Instructions" link instructions }

@{b}Version 1.0 (20th February 1997)@{ub}

  1st public release.

@{b}Version 1.01 (2nd April 1997)@{ub}

  Fixed savefile lock bug; File lock wasn't released after save and it made saved file unreadable until reset.

@{b}Version 1.10 (20nd April 1997)@{ub}

  Fixed misfeature in window showing hand evaluation. It now remembers its last position. Added option to enable/disable @{"Double Dialog" link double }. Savefile lock bug detected (again :-( ).

@{b}Version 1.11 (24nd April 1997)@{ub}

  Fixed savefile lock bug by replacing faulty GNU C/C++ libnix ?fstream class by my own cFile class. Changed savefile format. It now saves the most of options.

  Please feel free to contact @{"Author" link author } for @{"bugreports" link bugreports }, ideas, gongratulations...
@EndNode


@Node bugreports "Reporting Bugs"
@{b}Reporting Bugs@{ub}
@wordwrap


  Before you report any bug.

  1) Check that you have latest version. Latest version is available in Aminet. The bug you are about to report may be already fixed in latest version.
  2) Try to repeat the bug. This is important because AmigaOS has no memory protection. Faulty program may cause errors to other program. If I can't repeat bug I can't be sure is there bug or not.


  What information @{"author" link author } require about the bug.

  1) Detailed description about bug/misfeature.
  2) Program version number.
  3) Procedure how to repeat the bug if possible.
  4) Some info about your system. Especially processor and operating system version.

@EndNode

